<h1 class="text-center mb-4">Help & Support</h1>

<div class="accordion" id="accordionExample">
    <div class="accordion-item">
      <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
        <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
           <h5>1. How do I create a new post on the blog?</h5> 
        </button>
      </h2>
      <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
        <div class="accordion-body">
            To create a new post, log in to your account and navigate to the dashboard. Look for the "Create Post" button, usually located prominently on the dashboard or in the navigation menu. Click on it, and you'll be directed to a form where you can input your post's title, content, and any relevant media. Once you've filled in the details, hit the "Publish" button, and your post will be live on the blog.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-item">
      <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
           <h5>2. Can I edit or delete my posts after publishing them?</h5> 
        </button>
      </h2>
      <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
        <div class="accordion-body">
            Yes, you can edit or delete your posts. Simply log in to your account, go to the dashboard, and find the "Manage Posts" section. Locate the post you want to modify or remove, and you'll find options to edit or delete it. Keep in mind that some platforms may have specific rules regarding edits, especially if the post has already garnered engagement.
        </div>
      </div>
